Cell.Text: [S] So how has it come to pass that a vampire of mixed blood is in the company of my daughter?
[S] So how has it come to pass that a vampire hunter is in the company of my daughter? | It pains me to think you'd travel with Serana under the guise of her protector in an effort to hunt me down.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ05ValericaIntroBranchTopic: You wanted to speak with me?

Cell.Text: Safe? You call bringing her here safe? Has she explained nothing to you?
This is no ruse. I want to keep her safe.
Coming from one who murders vampires as a trade, I find it hard to believe your intentions are noble.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ05ValericaIntroBranchTopic01: I've been keeping her safe.

Cell.Text: [S] And how exactly do you plan on stopping him?
I would never allow that to happen.
[S] And how exactly do you plan on completing the prophecy without the death of my daughter?

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ05ValericaIntroBranchTopic02: I would never allow that to happen.

Cell.Text: If you believe that, then you're a bigger fool than I originally suspected. Don't you think I weighed that option before I enacted my plans?

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ05ValericaIntroBranchTopic03: I'll kill Harkon.

Cell.Text: You think I'd have the audacity to place my own daughter in that tomb for the protection of her Elder Scroll alone? | The scrolls are merely a means to an end. The key to the Tyranny of the Sun is Serana herself.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ05ValericaIntroBranchTopic01a: That's why I'm here for the Elder Scroll.

Cell.Text: If Harkon obtained Auriel's Bow and Serana's Blood was used to taint the weapon, the Tyranny of the Sun would be complete. | In his eyes, she'd be dying for the good of all vampires.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ05ValericaIntroBranchTopic01b: Are you saying Harkon means to kill her?

Cell.Text: [S] Your intentions are still somewhat unclear to me. | But for Serana's sake, I'll assist you in any way that I can.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ05ValericaIntroBranchPostTopic: What is your decision?

Cell.Text: You need to locate the tallest of the rocky spires that surround these ruins. | At their base, the barrier's energy is being drawn from unfortunate souls that have been exiled here. | Destroy the Keepers that are tending them, and it should bring the barrier down.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ05ValericaIntroBranchPostTopic01: What do we need to do?

Cell.Text: [S] One more word of warning. There's a dragon that calls itself Durnehviir roaming the Cairn. Be wary of him. | The Ideal Masters have charged him with overseeing the Keepers, and will undoubtedly intervene if you're perceived as a threat.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ05ValericaIntroBranchPostTopic02: We'll return soon.

Cell.Text: [S] G|Serana?

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ05ValericaIntroBranchTopic05: Serana believes in me, why won't you?

Cell.Text: I find your choice of words quite interesting considering that Serana is in far more danger now than she was following my "foolish plan."

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ05ValericaIntroBranchTopic01aa: I've saved her from your foolish plan.

Cell.Text: [S] Serana has sacrificed everything to prevent Harkon from completing the prophecy. I would have expected her to explain that to you.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ05ValericaIntroBranchTopic1aad

Cell.Text: Glorious. Serana claims your her guardian, yet your first instinct appears to be greed. I see that my daughter is still as naive as ever.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ05ValericaIntroBranchTopic01aab: I'm just here for the Elder Scroll.

Cell.Text: When I fled Castle Volkihar, I fled with two Elder Scrolls. | The scroll I presume you found with Serana speaks of Auriel and his arcane weapon, Auriel's Bow. | The second scroll declares that "The Blood of Coldharbour's Daughter will blind the eye of the Dragon."

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ05ValericaIntroBranchTopic01bb: What do you mean?

Cell.Text: Like myself, Serana was a human once. We were devout followers of Lord Molag-Bal. | Tradition dictates the females be offered to Molag-Bal on his summoning day. Few survive the ordeal. Those that do emerge as a pure-blooded vampire. | We call such confluences the "Daughters of Coldharbour."

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ05ValericaIntroBranchTopic01bc: How does Serana fit in?

Cell.Text: Now you're beginning to see why I wanted to protect Serana and why I've kept the other Elder Scroll as far from her as possible.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ05ValericaIntroBranchTopic01bd: The Tyranny of the Sun requires Serana's blood?

Cell.Text: Have you been listening to me? Like Serana, I'm a pure-blooded vampire. My presence on Tamriel is as much of a danger as hers.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ05ValericaIntroBranchTopic03a: I'll need your help.

Cell.Text: No! I will not allow that happen. The Elder Scrolls only tells of events that might be, not events that will be.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ05ValericaIntroBranchTopic03c: Perhaps her death is destined.

Cell.Text: You care nothing for Serana or our plight. | You're here because we're abominations in your mind. Evil creatures that need to be destroyed.
You care nothing for Serana or our plight. | You see the Tyranny of the Sun as your chance at deification, and like Harkon you won't hesitate to destroy anything that stands in your path.

You care nothing for Serana or our plight. | Whether or not you've become one of us in order to survive the Soul Cairn, you're still a vampire hunter at heart. | You're here because we're abominations in your mind. Evil creatures that need to be destroyed.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ05ValericaIntroBranchTopic03d: And Serana's opinion in this?

Cell.Text: It was expected of her, just as it was expected of me. | Being selected as an offering to Molag-Bal is an honor. She wouldn't have dared turn her back on that.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ05ValericaIntroBranchTopic01be: Serana underwent this ritual willingly?

Cell.Text: It's what some call the domain of Molag-Bal. His place in Oblivion.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ05ValericaIntroBranchTopic01bf: Coldharbour?

Cell.Text: [S] Yes. I've kept it safely secured here ever since I was imprisoned. | Fortunately, you're in a position to breach the barrier that surrounds these ruins.
Yes. I've kept it safely secured here ever since I was imprisoned. | Fortunately, you seem to have already killed the Keepers maintaining the barrier around these ruins.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ05ValericaIntroBranchPostTopic01a: Do you have the Elder Scroll with you?

Cell.Text: [S] I see. You're simply here to stop the Tyranny of the Sun, despite the cost to Serana. Nothing else matters.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ05ValericaIntroBranchTopic05a: I'm just here for the Elder Scroll.

Cell.Text: [S] G|Yes. Please, follow me. | One more word of warning. There's a dragon that calls itself Durnehviir roaming the Cairn. | The Ideal Masters have charged him with overseeing the Keepers, and will undoubtedly investigate the fact that the barrier has fallen.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ05ValericaIntroBranchPostTopic01b: Does that mean you can take us to it now?
